external_knowledge:
External knowledge is required to understand that the question refers to games between teams, where the winning team is the one with the higher score; 
the prediction accuracy refers to whether the predicted outcome matched the actual game result; 
the confidence score represents the model's confidence in its prediction; 
the score difference is the difference in points between the winning and losing teams; 
the cumulative correct predictions refer to the running total of correct predictions over time; 
and the average score difference per team is the average difference in scores for each team across all their games.
